jQuery.showPasswordField 
-------------------------

jQuery plugin that displays the password field value in cleartext. 
For now it just has two options

  type: 'checkbox' or 'hover'
  text: 'text to display next to password field'

default type is checkbox.

Usage: 
   $(password_field_descriptor).showPasswordField()
   $(password_field_descriptor).showPasswordField({type:'hover'})
   $(password_field_descriptor).showPasswordField({type:'checkbox'})
   $("input[type=password]").showPasswordField({option:'hover', text:'Hover the password field to
   see it in clear text'});

If type is hover, value in password field is displayed in cleartext when user hovers the 
password field with mouse.

If type is checkbox, a checkbox field is displayed next to password field. When checked,
password field is displayed in cleartext.


This plugin is derived from Davin Granroth's jquery.showPasswordCheckbox.js 
You can find the original plugin at http://blog.davingranroth.com/

